I don't know if this is a bug or a feature :) That's why I marked this as a fug :)

Anyway, I've realized that multiple different actions/transitions (ActionDescriptors) can share the same id. As a test, create a new workflow by copying an existing workflow. Then consider the following code example:

JiraWorkflow jw = ComponentAccessor.getWorkflowManager().getWorkflow("jira");
Collection<ActionDescriptor> workflowActions = workflow.getAllActions();
for (ActionDescriptor ad : workflowActions)
	log.info(jw.getName() + ":" + ad.getId() + ":" + ad.getName());

If you analyze the output, you'll see that in different workflows, all the actions have ids that start from 1, which makes 2 actions from 2 different workflows have the same id, which is very ambiguous imho.

To confirm those are really 2 different transitions, try editing a workflow, changing one of the existing transitions (change the name, destination step, etc). It will still appear with the same id as some other, completely different, transition (from another workflow).

